Here=E2=80=99s the twist, though: I=E2=80=99m actually not sure that these =
models are a threat to Google after all. This is truly the next step beyond=
 social media, where you are not just getting content from your network (Fa=
cebook), or even content from across the service (TikTok), but getting cont=
ent tailored to you. And let me tell you, it is incredibly engrossing, even=
 if it is, for now, a roguelike experience to get to the good stuff.

There are more stories of users feeling devastated by the change instituted=
 by Replika-owner Luka, including this one in Business Insider ( https://ww=
w.businessinsider.com/replika-chatbot-users-dont-like-nsfw-sexual-content-b=
ans-2023-2 ) and this first-person account in Wired ( https://www.wired.com=
/story/replika-chatbot-sexuality-ai/ ). What seems particularly nefarious i=
s the contention by many users on the Replika Subreddit ( https://www.reddi=
t.com/r/replika/ ) that the app had advertised its NSFW-capabilities as a m=
eans of getting users to subscribe for $69.99/year, only to lobotomize thei=
r new lovers.

Replika is, needless to say, a centralized service, like all such models; i=
t follows that this is an obvious application space for open source models =
that run locally, and that there is already a market. And, as the Reuters a=
rticle notes, this is hardly an unknown phenomenon when it comes to new tec=
hnology: porn is allegedly a significant factor in the victory of VHS over =
Betamax ( https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/nov/10/betamax-dead-l=
ong-live-vhs-sony-end-prodution ) , and has obviously played a major role i=
n multiple facets of the Internet, from the open web to peer-to-peer file s=
haring to streaming video to OnlyFans. That there would be demand for simul=
ated intimacy provided by AI should be obvious, and, once the models are ca=
pable, straight-up pornography as well.

Now one could probably write a thesis about the differences and similaritie=
s between something like Lily Rose and a porn star, although the para-socia=
l relationships on sites like OnlyFans obviously blur the lines; what matte=
rs for the purpose of this update is the the certainty that any large tech =
company will shy away from them, and that centralized AI services will ban =
them completely.

Apple, meanwhile, is famously anti-pornography: Safari can load whatever si=
te you want, but apps have a strict leash on them, and Apple has always err=
ed towards too strict over too lenient, including restricting apps with use=
r-generated content that didn=E2=80=99t police sexual content. It seems ver=
y likely that when and if iPhone apps gain the ability to run local models =
that Apple will retain strict control on what is in the App Store. What is =
notable, though, is there is a market here that Apple is uniquely positione=
d to enable and benefit from.

