My personal experience with Workrooms didn=E2=80=99t involve any dancing or=
 fitness; it was simply a conversation with the folks that built Workrooms.=
 The sense of presence, though, was tangible. Voices came from the right pl=
ace, thanks to Workrooms=E2=80=99 spatial audio, and hand gestures and view=
ing directions really made it feel like the three of us were in the same ro=
om. What was particularly compelling was the way that Workrooms=E2=80=99 vi=
rtual reality space seamlessly interfaced with the real world.

I see no reason why Apple=E2=80=99s headset wouldn=E2=80=99t deliver the sa=
me sort of experience, but like Meta ( https://stratechery.com/2022/meta-me=
